they wrote in "Cell," where they did similar work, not with TJPAB but the idea is

957
00:56:11.122 --> 00:56:15.102
very similar. They can create synthetic promoters, and you can modify the

958
00:56:15.142 --> 00:56:18.362
enhancer binding elements, and you can play with them in terms of number of

959
00:56:18.402 --> 00:56:22.102
elements and what elements with what promoter to create a given

960
00:56:22.402 --> 00:56:26.292
sensor, essentially. And that's what essentially we did, except for TJPAB.

961
00:56:26.842 --> 00:56:28.042
Okay, thanks a lot, Rizwan.

962
00:56:28.162 --> 00:56:28.352
Thank you.

963
00:56:28.352 --> 00:56:28.782
Thanks a lot.

964
00:56:31.262 --> 00:56:32.502
So nice transition

965
00:56:33.662 --> 00:56:36.922
to Tim Lu from Senti Bioscience,

966
00:56:37.822 --> 00:56:40.942
who will tell us about new cells to fight cancer.

967
00:56:41.322 --> 00:56:41.542
Great.

968
00:56:41.622 --> 00:56:41.902
Thanks.

969
00:56:43.402 --> 00:56:46.162
All right. Well, it's an honor to be here. My name is Tim.

970
00:56:46.702 --> 00:56:49.942
I was previously at MIT, and I left a few years ago to try to take some of these

